Oh there'd be fields near - nearby end on the shoredruck and the pottery shoredruck you know. The shoredruck, where - what - the sho
redruck is what used be - they called it in those days - where the potteries - potteries works - used to tip the shraf - the shraf is the - the stuff as is all been broken up, saggers and all that sort of stuff. Broken pottery and - pottery's as been smas
h
ed up, and it's been - wheeled out or - taken out on a trolley and - tipped. Same as it might be tipping it in a hole and - used to get full of - saggers and marl and - and - broken crockery and all that stuff that has all been - discarded. Well we used t
o play anywhere. Anywhere as long as you got somewhere to get out of the road a bit you know.
